Date: 0/3/1988
Source: More Magazine
Author:
Vol / Page: 31
Edition:
Quote: In sheds shearing fine wool (from Merino, Halfbred or Corriedale sheep) a woolclasser is employed to make lines of wool; that is, to define the differences between wool from each sheep after it has been shorn and skirted (dirty and shorter edges removed) by the shedhands, and to group similar wools together in baled lines for ease of sale and subsequent processing.
